{"Body":"<p>It's a type of <strong>appeal to emotion</strong>, specifically an <strong>appeal to flattery</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>The first part of the statement is an example of <a href=\"http://rhetoric.byu.edu/Figures/A/antiphrasis.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>antiphrasis</strong></a> It can also be considered a <strong>red herring</strong>, since it is intended to distract from the negative second part.</p>\n\n<p>Like a <strong><em>dissoi logoi</em></strong>, but with a different intention.</p>\n\n<p>Related terms:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://rhetoric.byu.edu/Figures/E/enantiosis.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rhetoric.byu.edu/Figures/E/enantiosis.htm</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://rhetoric.byu.edu/Figures/A/antitheton.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rhetoric.byu.edu/Figures/A/antitheton.htm</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BaitAndSwitchComment\" rel=\"nofollow\">TV Tropes calls it a <strong>bait-and-switch comment</strong></a>.</p>\n", "Id":"2562", "ParentId":"2561", "LastEditorUserId":"1021", "CreationDate":"2012-09-16T05:51:25.010", "OwnerUserId":"1021", "PostTypeId":"2", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2012-09-16T06:10:47.663", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"176", "WebsiteUrl":"https://launchpad.net/~replicator-snail", "ProfileImageUrl":"http://i.stack.imgur.com/KPUcH.png", "Id":"1021", "AccountId":"124682", "CreationDate":"2012-05-18T02:34:01.443", "AboutMe":"<p>. Native speaker of American English. Linux user. Familiar with several programming languages in the procedural, OO, and functional paradigms.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://codegolf.stackexchange.com/a/6855/2276\">Worst Code Golf ever</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://meta.stackoverflow.com/a/157374/146243\">New badge proposals!</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/fortune-mod/+bug/612986\" rel=\"nofollow\">Shakespeare bug in Ubuntu</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/122120/the-great-question-deletion-audit-of-2012/122207#122207\">The Great Question Deletion Audit of 2012</a></strong></li>\n<li>Chat\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/2495/terrifying-nightmare-monsters\">Horrible spiders</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/2110/aww\">Adorable fluffy things</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/1701/firearms\">LASERS!</a></strong></li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Link_rot\" rel=\"nofollow\">Link rot</a> is evil. <a href=\"http://archive.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Archive</a> <a href=\"http://www.archiveteam.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">everything</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keyboard_shortcut\" rel=\"nofollow\">The keyboard is king</a>. Correctness over performance. Canonicalize, normalize, deduplicate. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself\" rel=\"nofollow\">Don't repeat yourself.</a> <a href=\"http://utf8everywhere.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">UTF-8 > UTF-16.</a> Use <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_typing\" rel=\"nofollow\">static typing</a>: good for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autocomplete\" rel=\"nofollow\">tooling</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IKVM.NET\" rel=\"nofollow\">Re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\" rel=\"nofollow\">use</a>; don't <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_invented_here\" rel=\"nofollow\">re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/reinvent_the_wheel\" rel=\"nofollow\">invent</a>. Correctness, then clarity, then concision and elegance. Play devil's advocate. First understand opponents' positions.</p>\n", "Location":"United States", "DownVotes":"7", "Views":"12", "Reputation":"1534", "DisplayName":"Mechanical snail", "LastAccessDate":"2013-06-02T04:51:14.103"}, "LastActivityDate":"2012-09-16T06:10:47.663", "Score":"5", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"176", "WebsiteUrl":"https://launchpad.net/~replicator-snail", "ProfileImageUrl":"http://i.stack.imgur.com/KPUcH.png", "Id":"1021", "AccountId":"124682", "CreationDate":"2012-05-18T02:34:01.443", "AboutMe":"<p>. Native speaker of American English. Linux user. Familiar with several programming languages in the procedural, OO, and functional paradigms.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://codegolf.stackexchange.com/a/6855/2276\">Worst Code Golf ever</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://meta.stackoverflow.com/a/157374/146243\">New badge proposals!</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/fortune-mod/+bug/612986\" rel=\"nofollow\">Shakespeare bug in Ubuntu</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/122120/the-great-question-deletion-audit-of-2012/122207#122207\">The Great Question Deletion Audit of 2012</a></strong></li>\n<li>Chat\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/2495/terrifying-nightmare-monsters\">Horrible spiders</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/2110/aww\">Adorable fluffy things</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/1701/firearms\">LASERS!</a></strong></li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Link_rot\" rel=\"nofollow\">Link rot</a> is evil. <a href=\"http://archive.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Archive</a> <a href=\"http://www.archiveteam.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">everything</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keyboard_shortcut\" rel=\"nofollow\">The keyboard is king</a>. Correctness over performance. Canonicalize, normalize, deduplicate. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself\" rel=\"nofollow\">Don't repeat yourself.</a> <a href=\"http://utf8everywhere.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">UTF-8 > UTF-16.</a> Use <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_typing\" rel=\"nofollow\">static typing</a>: good for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autocomplete\" rel=\"nofollow\">tooling</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IKVM.NET\" rel=\"nofollow\">Re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\" rel=\"nofollow\">use</a>; don't <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_invented_here\" rel=\"nofollow\">re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/reinvent_the_wheel\" rel=\"nofollow\">invent</a>. Correctness, then clarity, then concision and elegance. Play devil's advocate. First understand opponents' positions.</p>\n", "Location":"United States", "DownVotes":"7", "Views":"12", "Reputation":"1534", "DisplayName":"Mechanical snail", "LastAccessDate":"2013-06-02T04:51:14.103"}}